1. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses the complexity of solving Mahjong Solitaire boards with peeking and proposes algorithms for solving them. This falls under the scope of data structures and algorithms. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes a practical algorithm for solving Mahjong Solitaire boards with peeking, which involves the use of heuristics and pruning criteria. This is a common area of research in artificial intelligence. 
3. cs.CG (Computational Geometry) - The paper discusses the layout of isolated stacks of heights one and two in Mahjong Solitaire and how they can be solved with peeking. This involves analyzing the geometric properties of the game board. 
4. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The paper discusses the complexity of solving Mahjong Solitaire boards with peeking, which is a game. This falls under the scope of game theory. 
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper discusses the complexity of solving Mahjong Solitaire boards with peeking and proves that it is NP-complete. This falls under the scope of computational complexity.
